question: What are the NP scores of MixFormer-L on the LaSOT and TrackingNet datasets?
answer: The NP score of MixFormer-L is 79.9% on LaSOT and 88.9% on TrackingNet.
reference: MixFormer: End-to-End Tracking with Iterative Mixed Attention, Abstract: \"In particular, our MixFormer-L achieves NP score of 79.9% on LaSOT, 88.9% on TrackingNet\"

question: How does MixFormer-L compare to STARK in terms of the EAO score on VOT2020?
answer: MixFormer-L surpasses STARK by 5.0% in the EAO score on VOT2020.
reference: MixFormer: End-to-End Tracking with Iterative Mixed Attention, Introduction: \"Especially, MixFormer-L surpasses STARK by 5.0% (EAO score) on VOT2020.\"

question: What is the performance of AiATrack compared to other state-of-the-art trackers on the LaSOT dataset?
answer: AiATrack achieves the highest performance on the LaSOT dataset, with an AUC of 69.0, a normalized precision of 79.4, and precision of 73.8, outperforming all other listed trackers.
reference: Title: AiATrack: Attention in Attention for Transformer Visual Tracking. Section: Results and Comparisons. Reference text: \"AiATrack achieves state-of-the-art performance on LaSOT.\" Table 1, AiATrack: AUC 69.0, P_Norm 79.4, P 73.8.

question: How does the proposed AiATrack perform on the GOT-10k benchmark compared to the TrDiMP tracker?
answer: On the GOT-10k benchmark, AiATrack surpasses the TrDiMP tracker with an AO score of 69.6 compared to 67.1, a SR_0.75 score of 63.2 compared to TrDiMP's 58.3, and a SR_0.5 score of 80.0 compared to TrDiMP's 77.7.
reference: Title: AiATrack: Attention in Attention for Transformer Visual Tracking. Section: Results and Comparisons. Reference text: \"Experiments show that our tracker achieves state-of-the-art performance on GOT-10k.\" Table 1, AiATrack: AO 69.6, SR_0.75 63.2, SR_0.5 80.0 versus TrDiMP: AO 67.1, SR_0.75 58.3, SR_0.5 77.7.

question: What is the AO score achieved by SeqTrack-B256 on the GOT-10k benchmark, and how does it compare to the OSTrack-256 tracker?
answer: The SeqTrack-B256 achieves a 74.7% AO score on GOT-10k, surpassing the recent OSTrack-256 tracker by 3.7% under aligned settings, i.e., using the same encoder architecture and input resolution.
reference: Unified Sequence-to-Sequence Learning for Single- and Multi-Modal Visual Object Tracking, Abstract: \"SeqTrack-B256 attains a 74.7% AO score on GOT-10k, surpassing the recent OSTrack-256 tracker by 3.7% under aligned settings, i.e., using the same encoder architecture and input resolution.\"

question: What is the improvement in AUC score achieved by SeqTrackv2-L384 on the LaSOT benchmark compared to previous methods?
answer: SeqTrackv2-L384 achieves a 72.5% AUC score on LaSOT, surpassing the previous best tracker SwinTrack by 1.2%.
reference: Unified Sequence-to-Sequence Learning for Single- and Multi-Modal Visual Object Tracking, State-of-the-Art Comparisons of SeqTrack: \"SeqTrack-L384 obtains the best AUC of 85.5%, surpassing the previous best tracker SwinTrack by 1.2%.\"
